    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{-18, 7, 8, 7, -17, 13, 13, 21, -9\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the **mean** of the data\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{-18 + 7 + 8 + 7 + (-17) + 13 + 13 + 21 + (-9)}{9}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{-18 + 7 + 8 + 7 - 17 + 13 + 13 + 21 - 9}{9}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{(-18 - 17 - 9) + (7 + 8 + 7 + 13 + 13 + 21)}{9}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{-44 + 68}{9} = \\frac{24}{9} = \\frac{8}{3}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the **deviations** from the mean\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n-18 - \\frac{8}{3} &= -\\frac{50}{3} \\\\\n7 - \\frac{8}{3} &= \\frac{13}{3} \\\\\n8 - \\frac{8}{3} &= \\frac{16}{3} \\\\\n7 - \\frac{8}{3} &= \\frac{13}{3} \\\\\n-17 - \\frac{8}{3} &= -\\frac{59}{3} \\\\\n13 - \\frac{8}{3} &= \\frac{31}{3} \\\\\n13 - \\frac{8}{3} &= \\frac{31}{3} \\\\\n21 - \\frac{8}{3} &= \\frac{55}{3} \\\\\n-9 - \\frac{8}{3} &= -\\frac{35}{3}\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Square each deviation\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n\\left(-\\frac{50}{3}\\right)^2 &= \\frac{2500}{9} \\\\\n\\left(\\frac{13}{3}\\right)^2 &= \\frac{169}{9}"
